---
/**
 * Displays a compact citation-quality legend explaining the green/yellow/red system.
 * Include on article pages or in the FAQ.
 */
---

<aside class="citation-legend" aria-label="Citation quality legend">
  <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">Citation Quality</h3>
  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
      <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 mt-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-emerald-500" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-fg-secondary)]">
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-fg-primary)]">Well-cited</strong> — Directly citing credible academic works; over 80% source-verified with only phrasing changes, no semantic difference.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
      <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 mt-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-amber-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-fg-secondary)]">
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-fg-primary)]">Derived from sources</strong> — Has citations but meaning and descriptions are interpreted or synthesized from sources; may not be fully accurate.
      </span>
    </li>
    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
      <span class="inline-block w-3 h-3 mt-1 rounded-full shrink-0 bg-red-500" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-fg-secondary)]">
        <strong class="text-[var(--color-fg-primary)]">Needs citation</strong> — Poor citation or lacks citation entirely. Treat with caution and consider contributing improved sources.
      </span>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">
    See <a href="/faq/#citation-quality" class="text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline">FAQ: Citation Quality</a> for full details.
  </p>
</aside>
